<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a10Jan1935"><font color="red">10 January 1935</font> <i>NLPL</i> (to Paul L&eacute;on): Also v. Mencken &ldquo;The American Language&rdquo; the exact meaning in slang of &lsquo;porkbarrel&rsquo; &hellip; I was working today but am quite flattened out by the news that all my money is gone. [in Paul L&eacute;on hand] humourous metaphor bugaboo / found in Political Americanisms by Ch. Norton N.Y and London 1890 &ldquo;origin political campaign when Jefferson defeated Adam pre civil war. Government appropriations that are used as political patronage to build up party power.&rdquo; Maurice Weseen <i>Dictionary of American Slang</i> 60 frs. </div>
